Adds new column to the fixations data frame with information about a fixation being within area bounds

EyerObject()

This function decides whether the list is acceptable

eye_to_unity_times()

find_better_match()

Returns either a list with best synchronised event or NULL if none is found

find_group_match()

tries to find a sequency of N elements in eye_durations that correspond to the synchro durations returns index of first matchin eye event

find_preprocessed_files()

returns filepaths of preprocessed fixations and events

find_unprocessed_file()

Returns list of eyetracker files of given eyetracker

is_data_loaded(<eyer>)

Returns if the eylinker object has both evens and fixations loaded

is_data_loaded()

Returns if the data is loaded

load_eyetracker_data()

Loads data from a folder. Loads preprocessed events and fixations files, or raw files if override is set to TRUE or if there are no preprocessed files

load_unprocessed_file()

Loads raw file and returns list with evens and fixations

open_unprocessed_file()

Finds and loads data from a directory

preprocess_eye_events()

Reads and cleans events

preprocess_eye_fixations()

Preprocesses loaded fixations. This usually means adding columns or recalculating values that are not not well read

read_calibrations()

Reads eyetracker calibration infromation from given file

read_eye_events()

read_eye_fixations()

read_eye_movements()

Reads movements from given file

read_resolution()

Reads eyetracker resolution from given file

remove_out_of_bounds_fixations()

Removes fixations out of disp_resolution boundary

SR1000.read_resolution()

match two digits at least three digit long after Display coords ? signifies non greedy match (as least as possible)

try_fit_event()

Returns a data frome with synchronising times for each set Table is in format of set_id, time_eyetracker, time_unity
